HEADWORD: lymantriid
<hw>lymantriid</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A dull-colored moth whose larvae
have tufts of hair on the body and feed on the leaves of many deciduous
trees.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> tussock moth.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lymantriidae</ent>⟦br⟧
